# ----- Rust build artefacts -----
/target/
**/target/
Cargo.lock.bak
*.rs.bk
*.pdb

# ----- Python environment (research tooling only) -----
.venv/
venv/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.mypy_cache/

# ----- Research & experimental tooling (gitignored until promoted) -----
#
# Default: everything under `research/` is gitignored. Exception below
# carves out `research/llm-fluency/` — the Phase 3.2 benchmark apparatus
# is load-bearing for the wire-surface existential gate, so the corpus
# + harness are tracked and reviewable *before* any run. Run outputs
# (reproducible from the committed apparatus) stay gitignored.
#
# Pattern: `research/*` (not `research/`) keeps the directory itself
# traversable so `!research/llm-fluency` can take effect. Git cannot
# re-include a file whose parent directory is excluded — see git-scm
# "PATTERN FORMAT" docs.
research/*
!research/llm-fluency
!research/recovery-benchmark
!research/librarian
research/llm-fluency/results/
research/llm-fluency/*.log
research/recovery-benchmark/results/
research/librarian/results/
experiments/

# ----- Fuzz / coverage runtime artefacts (never committed) -----
fuzz/artifacts/
fuzz/coverage/
*.profraw
*.profdata

# ----- Machine-local Claude Code state (user-specific, never committed) -----
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/settings.json
.claude/skills/

# ----- Mimir operator-local state (per-operator workspace data, never committed) -----
.mimir/

# ----- Scratch & debug output -----
*.log
out.txt
scratch_*
*.tmp
build_*.txt
test_*.txt

# ----- OS noise -----
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# ----- IDE state -----
.idea/
.vscode/
*.code-workspace
.helix/
*.swp
*.swo
